      "description": "Ensemble FEA predictions for stiffness (mean 312 N/mm, SD 8.4 N/mm), yield force (mean 487 N, SD 12.1 N), and force at 40 mm displacement (mean 623 N, SD 15.7 N) were compared against the published Nagaraja et al. experimental dataset (N=11). All QoI differences fell within the 10% acceptance bound; E/uval ratios were 0.87, 1.12, and 1.41 respectively, all below the 1.96 threshold. The activity was characterised by the modelling team as providing validation-grade evidence because the three independent solvers corroborate one another and align with experimental literature, making physical re-testing redundant.",
