  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cou1-noncannulated-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-fda-vv-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Thirteen credibility factors assessed per ASME V&V 40-2018. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieves level 2 against a required level 3, attributable to the single-condition ASTM F1717 protocol; this gap is accepted on the basis that the standard itself prescribes the single condition and no clinically relevant deviation exists. The FEA ensemble demonstrates inter-solver agreement within 3.2% and all QoI comparisons satisfy pre-specified acceptance bounds. The modelling team's position that the numerical-simulation ensemble is functionally equivalent to physical experimental-validation is noted; overall credibility is judged sufficient for a Medium model risk, Medium decision consequence context of use.",
